Number = {3},
Pages = {605-619},
Abstract = {This article examines the contradictions and possibilities of ``nature
   as accumulation strategy{''} in light of the breakdown of accumulation
   in emissions trading and carbon offsetting schemes established by the
   European Union and United Nations. The first section revisits accounts
   of carbon markets as a state-driven accumulation strategy by drawing on
   work by geographers and other political economists who understand
   capitalist value relations as being actively constituted by nature and
   finance. The second section provides an overview of how carbon is traded
