Month = {NOV-DEC},
Abstract = {The resources invested by the forest owner in the nature conservation of
   the forest depend on the level of nature conservation, the efficiency of
   the production and the distribution of costs between the forest owner
   and other groups. The level of nature conservation is increasing Ly the
   change of values outside but also inside forestry, whereas a reduction
   of the level is caused by the reorganization of the state owned forests.
   The increase of the efficiency in securing nature values in the forest
   helps forestry to bring the costs down. This carl be achieved by
   integrating the god of nature conservation into multifunctional forestry
   and by cooperation with new environmentalist experts. The forest owner
   could get additional financial resources for nature values of his forest
   by selling new non-wood products. But such redistributional policy
